101071203.description:
The second swordplay derived from Eastwind Slash. The extraordinary and the everyday, the forceful and the soft, all in one.
When in the <material=underline c=#FFFFFF h=2 event=terminology args=(107101)>Still stance</material>: This skill is replaced by Eternal Prosperity: Wind. Skill may only be cast when Divine Grace is at max. Launches a flying sword that deals Wind DMG equal to <color=#E78300>{1}</color> ATK in total. As it flies, the sword summons up to <color=#E78300>8</color> <material=underline c=#FFFFFF h=2 event=terminology args=(107105)>Thundercloud Strikes</material> that hit enemies along the way. After catching the sword, Mod switches to the <material=underline c=#FFFFFF h=2 event=terminology args=(107102)>Move stance</material>, removes all <material=underline c=#FFFFFF h=2 event=terminology args=(107103)>Nay</material> Marks, resets the CD of Eternal Prosperity: Thunder, and hurls the sword again, dealing Thunder DMG equal to <color=#E78300>{7}</color> ATK in total at the location of the first enemy hit and summons <color=#E78300>6</color> <material=underline c=#FFFFFF h=2 event=terminology args=(107105)>Thundercloud Strikes</material> to attack targets within the area and slightly gather enemies. Switches to the <material=underline c=#FFFFFF h=2 event=terminology args=(107101)>Still stance</material> when Divine Grace is at <color=#E78300>0</color>.
<material=underline c=#FFFFFF h=2 event=terminology args=(107105)>Thundercloud Strike</material>: Deals Thunder DMG equal to <color=#E78300>{2}</color> ATK.
When in the <material=underline c=#FFFFFF h=2 event=terminology args=(107102)>Move stance</material>: This skill is replaced by Eternal Prosperity: Thunder. Expends up to <color=#E78300>15</color> Divine Grace, dealing DMG over three strikes, with the final strike summoning <color=#E78300>10</color> <material=underline c=#FFFFFF h=2 event=terminology args=(107105)>Thundercloud Strikes</material> in the area ahead. Depending on when Aero Break is cast alternately with this skill, four follow-on sword moves occur, and each dealing different damage.
Move 1: Casting Aero Break directly to deal a total of <color=#E78300>{3}</color> ATK as Thunder DMG;
Move 2: Casting Aero Break before the second strike for up to <color=#E78300>{4}</color> ATK as Thunder DMG;
Move 3: Casting Aero Break before the third strike for up to <color=#E78300>{5}</color> ATK as Thunder DMG;
Move 4: Casting Aero Break before both the second and third strikes for up to <color=#E78300>{6}</color> ATK as Thunder DMG.
